{"id":1261852951,"name":"ERD_project","description":"A lightning-fast, beautifully designed, code-to-diagram ERD tool.","html_url":"https://github.com/JaberChowdhury/ERD_project","homepage":"https://erd-project.vercel.app/","language":"TypeScript","topics":["agentic-ai","canvas","erd","erdiagram","postgresql","react","sql","tailwindcss","tool","typescript"],"stargazers_count":1,"updated_at":"2026-06-17T08:54:31Z","full_name":"JaberChowdhury/ERD_project","watchers_count":1,"forks_count":0,"pushed_at":"2026-06-13T16:54:59Z","default_branch":"main","fork":false,"size":396,"open_issues_count":0,"branches":[{"name":"main","commit":{"sha":"a7f0d52af87baa7678c1d7d381eb6d38cf0ac0e6","url":"https://api.github.com/repos/JaberChowdhury/ERD_project/commits/a7f0d52af87baa7678c1d7d381eb6d38cf0ac0e6"},"protected":false,"languages":{"Markdown":5,"TypeScript":19,"CSS":2,"React":16,"JSON":3,"JavaScript":3},"recentCommits":[{"sha":"a7f0d52af87baa7678c1d7d381eb6d38cf0ac0e6","message":"update & add : some bug and new features","author":"Jaber","date":"2026-06-13T16:54:57Z","url":"https://github.com/JaberChowdhury/ERD_project/commit/a7f0d52af87baa7678c1d7d381eb6d38cf0ac0e6"},{"sha":"93d98bb4afa4bef2818eea06b7c9b739d8958621","message":"refactor: replace persistent SQLite storage with an in-memory map and remove better-sqlite3 dependency","author":"Jaber","date":"2026-06-12T19:19:20Z","url":"https://github.com/JaberChowdhury/ERD_project/commit/93d98bb4afa4bef2818eea06b7c9b739d8958621"},{"sha":"0a136e79974ec3835df721b7a5bed28b0f80dfe0","message":"refactor: obfuscate dynamic require in database driver to prevent static analysis issues","author":"Jaber","date":"2026-06-12T19:16:00Z","url":"https://github.com/JaberChowdhury/ERD_project/commit/0a136e79974ec3835df721b7a5bed28b0f80dfe0"},{"sha":"2aa7a03bb76ce96aa797f3fc5bc8af630e30f797","message":"fix: add support for better-sqlite3 as a fallback for non-Bun environments","author":"Jaber","date":"2026-06-12T19:12:44Z","url":"https://github.com/JaberChowdhury/ERD_project/commit/2aa7a03bb76ce96aa797f3fc5bc8af630e30f797"},{"sha":"bef6304f909fd19e39947a732da9d3286853e794","message":"fixed : build command and dependency error","author":"Jaber","date":"2026-06-12T18:36:33Z","url":"https://github.com/JaberChowdhury/ERD_project/commit/bef6304f909fd19e39947a732da9d3286853e794"}]}],"readmes":[{"name":"main","readmeHtml":"<div id=\"readme\" class=\"md\" data-path=\"README.md\"><article class=\"markdown-body entry-content container-lg\" itemprop=\"text\"><div align=\"center\" dir=\"auto\">\n  <div dir=\"auto\">\n    \n  </div>\n  <div class=\"markdown-heading\" dir=\"auto\"><h1 class=\"heading-element\" dir=\"auto\">Schema Canvas</h1><a id=\"user-content-schema-canvas\" class=\"anchor\" aria-label=\"Permalink: Schema Canvas\" href=\"#schema-canvas\"><svg data-component=\"Octicon\" class=\"octicon octicon-link\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" version=\"1.1\" width=\"16\" height=\"16\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><path d=\"m7.775 3.275 1.25-1.25a3.5 3.5 0 1 1 4.95 4.95l-2.5 2.5a3.5 3.5 0 0 1-4.95 0 .751.751 0 0 1 .018-1.042.751.751 0 0 1 1.042-.018 1.998 1.998 0 0 0 2.83 0l2.5-2.5a2.002 2.002 0 0 0-2.83-2.83l-1.25 1.25a.751.751 0 0 1-1.042-.018.751.751 0 0 1-.018-1.042Zm-4.69 9.64a1.998 1.998 0 0 0 2.83 0l1.25-1.25a.751.751 0 0 1 1.042.018.751.751 0 0 1 .018 1.042l-1.25 1.25a3.5 3.5 0 1 1-4.95-4.95l2.5-2.5a3.5 3.5 0 0 1 4.95 0 .751.751 0 0 1-.018 1.042.751.751 0 0 1-1.042.018 1.998 1.998 0 0 0-2.83 0l-2.5 2.5a1.998 1.998 0 0 0 0 2.83Z\"></path></svg></a></div>\n  <p dir=\"auto\"><strong>A lightning-fast, beautifully designed, code-to-diagram ERD tool.</strong></p>\n</div>\n<hr>\n<p dir=\"auto\">Schema Canvas is a modern, Material You-styled web application that compiles a custom Domain Specific Language (DSL) into a stunning, interactive Entity Relationship Diagram (ERD) in real-time.</p>\n<div class=\"markdown-heading\" dir=\"auto\"><h2 class=\"heading-element\" dir=\"auto\">✨ Key Features</h2><a id=\"user-content--key-features\" class=\"anchor\" aria-label=\"Permalink: ✨ Key Features\" href=\"#-key-features\"><svg data-component=\"Octicon\" class=\"octicon octicon-link\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" version=\"1.1\" width=\"16\" height=\"16\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><path d=\"m7.775 3.275 1.25-1.25a3.5 3.5 0 1 1 4.95 4.95l-2.5 2.5a3.5 3.5 0 0 1-4.95 0 .751.751 0 0 1 .018-1.042.751.751 0 0 1 1.042-.018 1.998 1.998 0 0 0 2.83 0l2.5-2.5a2.002 2.002 0 0 0-2.83-2.83l-1.25 1.25a.751.751 0 0 1-1.042-.018.751.751 0 0 1-.018-1.042Zm-4.69 9.64a1.998 1.998 0 0 0 2.83 0l1.25-1.25a.751.751 0 0 1 1.042.018.751.751 0 0 1 .018 1.042l-1.25 1.25a3.5 3.5 0 1 1-4.95-4.95l2.5-2.5a3.5 3.5 0 0 1 4.95 0 .751.751 0 0 1-.018 1.042.751.751 0 0 1-1.042.018 1.998 1.998 0 0 0-2.83 0l-2.5 2.5a1.998 1.998 0 0 0 0 2.83Z\"></path></svg></a></div>\n<ul dir=\"auto\">\n<li><strong>Real-Time Rendering</strong>: Type your schema and watch the visual graph compile and route itself instantly using the powerful Dagre layout engine.</li>\n<li><strong>Material You Aesthetic</strong>: Built with dynamic, tonal surface colors and pill-shaped interactive elements that feel native, responsive, and incredibly premium.</li>\n<li><strong>Dynamic Theming</strong>: Flawless Light, Dark, and System theme synchronization.</li>\n<li><strong>Deep Customization</strong>: Adjust horizontal/vertical gaps, toggle Bezier vs. Orthogonal paths, customize font families (Inter, Roboto, Fira Code, Outfit), and tweak corner radii on the fly.</li>\n<li><strong>Flawless Export Engine</strong>: Export your diagrams directly to high-res <code>PNG</code> or crisp <code>SVG</code> with all of your custom canvas settings perfectly preserved.</li>\n<li><strong>URL Serialization</strong>: Share your schema <em>and</em> your layout settings instantly via compressed URL payloads!</li>\n</ul>\n<hr>\n<div class=\"markdown-heading\" dir=\"auto\"><h2 class=\"heading-element\" dir=\"auto\">📖 The Schema DSL</h2><a id=\"user-content--the-schema-dsl\" class=\"anchor\" aria-label=\"Permalink: 📖 The Schema DSL\" href=\"#-the-schema-dsl\"><svg data-component=\"Octicon\" class=\"octicon octicon-link\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" version=\"1.1\" width=\"16\" height=\"16\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><path d=\"m7.775 3.275 1.25-1.25a3.5 3.5 0 1 1 4.95 4.95l-2.5 2.5a3.5 3.5 0 0 1-4.95 0 .751.751 0 0 1 .018-1.042.751.751 0 0 1 1.042-.018 1.998 1.998 0 0 0 2.83 0l2.5-2.5a2.002 2.002 0 0 0-2.83-2.83l-1.25 1.25a.751.751 0 0 1-1.042-.018.751.751 0 0 1-.018-1.042Zm-4.69 9.64a1.998 1.998 0 0 0 2.83 0l1.25-1.25a.751.751 0 0 1 1.042.018.751.751 0 0 1 .018 1.042l-1.25 1.25a3.5 3.5 0 1 1-4.95-4.95l2.5-2.5a3.5 3.5 0 0 1 4.95 0 .751.751 0 0 1-.018 1.042.751.751 0 0 1-1.042.018 1.998 1.998 0 0 0-2.83 0l-2.5 2.5a1.998 1.998 0 0 0 0 2.83Z\"></path></svg></a></div>\n<p dir=\"auto\">The syntax is designed to be as minimal and intuitive as possible.</p>\n<div class=\"markdown-heading\" dir=\"auto\"><h3 class=\"heading-element\" dir=\"auto\">1. Defining Tables</h3><a id=\"user-content-1-defining-tables\" class=\"anchor\" aria-label=\"Permalink: 1. Defining Tables\" href=\"#1-defining-tables\"><svg data-component=\"Octicon\" class=\"octicon octicon-link\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" version=\"1.1\" width=\"16\" height=\"16\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><path d=\"m7.775 3.275 1.25-1.25a3.5 3.5 0 1 1 4.95 4.95l-2.5 2.5a3.5 3.5 0 0 1-4.95 0 .751.751 0 0 1 .018-1.042.751.751 0 0 1 1.042-.018 1.998 1.998 0 0 0 2.83 0l2.5-2.5a2.002 2.002 0 0 0-2.83-2.83l-1.25 1.25a.751.751 0 0 1-1.042-.018.751.751 0 0 1-.018-1.042Zm-4.69 9.64a1.998 1.998 0 0 0 2.83 0l1.25-1.25a.751.751 0 0 1 1.042.018.751.751 0 0 1 .018 1.042l-1.25 1.25a3.5 3.5 0 1 1-4.95-4.95l2.5-2.5a3.5 3.5 0 0 1 4.95 0 .751.751 0 0 1-.018 1.042.751.751 0 0 1-1.042.018 1.998 1.998 0 0 0-2.83 0l-2.5 2.5a1.998 1.998 0 0 0 0 2.83Z\"></path></svg></a></div>\n<p dir=\"auto\">Tables are defined by their name, optional metadata inside brackets <code>[]</code>, and a block of fields.</p>\n<div class=\"highlight highlight-source-ts notranslate position-relative overflow-auto\" dir=\"auto\" data-snippet-clipboard-copy-content=\"tableName [icon: database, color: purple] {\n  id string pk\n  username string\n  createdAt timestamp\n}\"><pre><span class=\"pl-s1\">tableName</span> <span class=\"pl-kos\">[</span><span class=\"pl-s1\">icon</span>: <span class=\"pl-s1\">database</span><span class=\"pl-kos\">,</span> <span class=\"pl-s1\">color</span>: <span class=\"pl-s1\">purple</span><span class=\"pl-kos\">]</span><span class=\"pl-kos\"></span> <span class=\"pl-kos\">{</span>\n  <span class=\"pl-s1\">id</span> <span class=\"pl-s1\">string</span> <span class=\"pl-s1\">pk</span>\n  <span class=\"pl-s1\">username</span> <span class=\"pl-s1\">string</span>\n  <span class=\"pl-s1\">createdAt</span> <span class=\"pl-s1\">timestamp</span>\n<span class=\"pl-kos\">}</span></pre></div>\n<div class=\"markdown-alert markdown-alert-note\" dir=\"auto\"><p class=\"markdown-alert-title\" dir=\"auto\"><svg data-component=\"Octicon\" class=\"octicon octicon-info mr-2\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" version=\"1.1\" width=\"16\" height=\"16\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><path d=\"M0 8a8 8 0 1 1 16 0A8 8 0 0 1 0 8Zm8-6.5a6.5 6.5 0 1 0 0 13 6.5 6.5 0 0 0 0-13ZM6.5 7.75A.75.75 0 0 1 7.25 7h1a.75.75 0 0 1 .75.75v2.75h.25a.75.75 0 0 1 0 1.5h-2a.75.75 0 0 1 0-1.5h.25v-2h-.25a.75.75 0 0 1-.75-.75ZM8 6a1 1 0 1 1 0-2 1 1 0 0 1 0 2Z\"></path></svg>Note</p><p dir=\"auto\"><strong>Metadata Options</strong></p>\n<ul dir=\"auto\">\n<li><code>icon</code>: Use any valid <a href=\"https://lucide.dev/icons/\" rel=\"nofollow\">Lucide-React</a> icon name (e.g., <code>user</code>, <code>shield</code>, <code>building</code>).</li>\n<li><code>color</code>: Use standard hex codes (<code>#123456</code>) or built-in named colors (<code>blue</code>, <code>red</code>, <code>purple</code>, <code>green</code>, <code>orange</code>).</li>\n<li><code>pk</code>: Append <code>pk</code> after a field type to visually flag it as a Primary Key!</li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n<div class=\"markdown-heading\" dir=\"auto\"><h3 class=\"heading-element\" dir=\"auto\">2. Defining Relationships</h3><a id=\"user-content-2-defining-relationships\" class=\"anchor\" aria-label=\"Permalink: 2. Defining Relationships\" href=\"#2-defining-relationships\"><svg data-component=\"Octicon\" class=\"octicon octicon-link\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" version=\"1.1\" width=\"16\" height=\"16\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><path d=\"m7.775 3.275 1.25-1.25a3.5 3.5 0 1 1 4.95 4.95l-2.5 2.5a3.5 3.5 0 0 1-4.95 0 .751.751 0 0 1 .018-1.042.751.751 0 0 1 1.042-.018 1.998 1.998 0 0 0 2.83 0l2.5-2.5a2.002 2.002 0 0 0-2.83-2.83l-1.25 1.25a.751.751 0 0 1-1.042-.018.751.751 0 0 1-.018-1.042Zm-4.69 9.64a1.998 1.998 0 0 0 2.83 0l1.25-1.25a.751.751 0 0 1 1.042.018.751.751 0 0 1 .018 1.042l-1.25 1.25a3.5 3.5 0 1 1-4.95-4.95l2.5-2.5a3.5 3.5 0 0 1 4.95 0 .751.751 0 0 1-.018 1.042.751.751 0 0 1-1.042.018 1.998 1.998 0 0 0-2.83 0l-2.5 2.5a1.998 1.998 0 0 0 0 2.83Z\"></path></svg></a></div>\n<p dir=\"auto\">Connect fields across tables using intuitive arrow operators outside of the table blocks:</p>\n<ul dir=\"auto\">\n<li><code>table1.id &lt;&gt; table2.ref</code> → <strong>Many-to-Many</strong></li>\n<li><code>table1.id &gt; table2.ref</code> → <strong>One-to-Many</strong></li>\n<li><code>table1.id &lt; table2.ref</code> → <strong>Many-to-One</strong></li>\n<li><code>table1.id - table2.ref</code> → <strong>One-to-One</strong></li>\n</ul>\n<div class=\"markdown-heading\" dir=\"auto\"><h3 class=\"heading-element\" dir=\"auto\">Example Schema</h3><a id=\"user-content-example-schema\" class=\"anchor\" aria-label=\"Permalink: Example Schema\" href=\"#example-schema\"><svg data-component=\"Octicon\" class=\"octicon octicon-link\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" version=\"1.1\" width=\"16\" height=\"16\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><path d=\"m7.775 3.275 1.25-1.25a3.5 3.5 0 1 1 4.95 4.95l-2.5 2.5a3.5 3.5 0 0 1-4.95 0 .751.751 0 0 1 .018-1.042.751.751 0 0 1 1.042-.018 1.998 1.998 0 0 0 2.83 0l2.5-2.5a2.002 2.002 0 0 0-2.83-2.83l-1.25 1.25a.751.751 0 0 1-1.042-.018.751.751 0 0 1-.018-1.042Zm-4.69 9.64a1.998 1.998 0 0 0 2.83 0l1.25-1.25a.751.751 0 0 1 1.042.018.751.751 0 0 1 .018 1.042l-1.25 1.25a3.5 3.5 0 1 1-4.95-4.95l2.5-2.5a3.5 3.5 0 0 1 4.95 0 .751.751 0 0 1-.018 1.042.751.751 0 0 1-1.042.018 1.998 1.998 0 0 0-2.83 0l-2.5 2.5a1.998 1.998 0 0 0 0 2.83Z\"></path></svg></a></div>\n<div class=\"snippet-clipboard-content notranslate position-relative overflow-auto\" data-snippet-clipboard-copy-content=\"users [icon: user, color: blue] {\n  id string pk\n  fullName string\n}\n\nroles [icon: shield, color: purple] {\n  id string pk\n  name string\n}\n\nuser_roles [icon: users, color: purple] {\n  userId string\n  roleId string\n}\n\nusers.id &lt;&gt; user_roles.userId\nroles.id &lt;&gt; user_roles.roleId\"><pre lang=\"text\" class=\"notranslate\"><code>users [icon: user, color: blue] {\n  id string pk\n  fullName string\n}\n\nroles [icon: shield, color: purple] {\n  id string pk\n  name string\n}\n\nuser_roles [icon: users, color: purple] {\n  userId string\n  roleId string\n}\n\nusers.id &lt;&gt; user_roles.userId\nroles.id &lt;&gt; user_roles.roleId\n</code></pre></div>\n<hr>\n<div class=\"markdown-heading\" dir=\"auto\"><h2 class=\"heading-element\" dir=\"auto\">🔗 URL Serialization (Sharing)</h2><a id=\"user-content--url-serialization-sharing\" class=\"anchor\" aria-label=\"Permalink: 🔗 URL Serialization (Sharing)\" href=\"#-url-serialization-sharing\"><svg data-component=\"Octicon\" class=\"octicon octicon-link\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" version=\"1.1\" width=\"16\" height=\"16\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><path d=\"m7.775 3.275 1.25-1.25a3.5 3.5 0 1 1 4.95 4.95l-2.5 2.5a3.5 3.5 0 0 1-4.95 0 .751.751 0 0 1 .018-1.042.751.751 0 0 1 1.042-.018 1.998 1.998 0 0 0 2.83 0l2.5-2.5a2.002 2.002 0 0 0-2.83-2.83l-1.25 1.25a.751.751 0 0 1-1.042-.018.751.751 0 0 1-.018-1.042Zm-4.69 9.64a1.998 1.998 0 0 0 2.83 0l1.25-1.25a.751.751 0 0 1 1.042.018.751.751 0 0 1 .018 1.042l-1.25 1.25a3.5 3.5 0 1 1-4.95-4.95l2.5-2.5a3.5 3.5 0 0 1 4.95 0 .751.751 0 0 1-.018 1.042.751.751 0 0 1-1.042.018 1.998 1.998 0 0 0-2.83 0l-2.5 2.5a1.998 1.998 0 0 0 0 2.83Z\"></path></svg></a></div>\n<p dir=\"auto\">When you click the <strong>Share</strong> button, Schema Canvas does not just save your code. It serializes both your schema and your active visual settings into a highly compressed URL hash using <code>lz-string</code>.</p>\n<div class=\"markdown-heading\" dir=\"auto\"><h3 class=\"heading-element\" dir=\"auto\">The Data Payload</h3><a id=\"user-content-the-data-payload\" class=\"anchor\" aria-label=\"Permalink: The Data Payload\" href=\"#the-data-payload\"><svg data-component=\"Octicon\" class=\"octicon octicon-link\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" version=\"1.1\" width=\"16\" height=\"16\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><path d=\"m7.775 3.275 1.25-1.25a3.5 3.5 0 1 1 4.95 4.95l-2.5 2.5a3.5 3.5 0 0 1-4.95 0 .751.751 0 0 1 .018-1.042.751.751 0 0 1 1.042-.018 1.998 1.998 0 0 0 2.83 0l2.5-2.5a2.002 2.002 0 0 0-2.83-2.83l-1.25 1.25a.751.751 0 0 1-1.042-.018.751.751 0 0 1-.018-1.042Zm-4.69 9.64a1.998 1.998 0 0 0 2.83 0l1.25-1.25a.751.751 0 0 1 1.042.018.751.751 0 0 1 .018 1.042l-1.25 1.25a3.5 3.5 0 1 1-4.95-4.95l2.5-2.5a3.5 3.5 0 0 1 4.95 0 .751.751 0 0 1-.018 1.042.751.751 0 0 1-1.042.018 1.998 1.998 0 0 0-2.83 0l-2.5 2.5a1.998 1.998 0 0 0 0 2.83Z\"></path></svg></a></div>\n<p dir=\"auto\">The internal payload structure looks like this before compression:</p>\n<div class=\"highlight highlight-source-json notranslate position-relative overflow-auto\" dir=\"auto\" data-snippet-clipboard-copy-content=\"{\n  &quot;code&quot;: &quot;users { id pk }&quot;,\n  &quot;settings&quot;: {\n    &quot;nodesep&quot;: 60,\n    &quot;ranksep&quot;: 250,\n    &quot;pathType&quot;: &quot;bezier&quot;,\n    &quot;fontFamily&quot;: &quot;'Inter', sans-serif&quot;,\n    &quot;borderRadius&quot;: &quot;2rem&quot;\n  }\n}\"><pre>{\n  <span class=\"pl-ent\">\"code\"</span>: <span class=\"pl-s\"><span class=\"pl-pds\">\"</span>users { id pk }<span class=\"pl-pds\">\"</span></span>,\n  <span class=\"pl-ent\">\"settings\"</span>: {\n    <span class=\"pl-ent\">\"nodesep\"</span>: <span class=\"pl-c1\">60</span>,\n    <span class=\"pl-ent\">\"ranksep\"</span>: <span class=\"pl-c1\">250</span>,\n    <span class=\"pl-ent\">\"pathType\"</span>: <span class=\"pl-s\"><span class=\"pl-pds\">\"</span>bezier<span class=\"pl-pds\">\"</span></span>,\n    <span class=\"pl-ent\">\"fontFamily\"</span>: <span class=\"pl-s\"><span class=\"pl-pds\">\"</span>'Inter', sans-serif<span class=\"pl-pds\">\"</span></span>,\n    <span class=\"pl-ent\">\"borderRadius\"</span>: <span class=\"pl-s\"><span class=\"pl-pds\">\"</span>2rem<span class=\"pl-pds\">\"</span></span>\n  }\n}</pre></div>\n<p dir=\"auto\">This ensures that whoever clicks your link sees the exact same layout, fonts, and gap spacing that you designed!</p>\n<div class=\"markdown-alert markdown-alert-tip\" dir=\"auto\"><p class=\"markdown-alert-title\" dir=\"auto\"><svg data-component=\"Octicon\" class=\"octicon octicon-light-bulb mr-2\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" version=\"1.1\" width=\"16\" height=\"16\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><path d=\"M8 1.5c-2.363 0-4 1.69-4 3.75 0 .984.424 1.625.984 2.304l.214.253c.223.264.47.556.673.848.284.411.537.896.621 1.49a.75.75 0 0 1-1.484.211c-.04-.282-.163-.547-.37-.847a8.456 8.456 0 0 0-.542-.68c-.084-.1-.173-.205-.268-.32C3.201 7.75 2.5 6.766 2.5 5.25 2.5 2.31 4.863 0 8 0s5.5 2.31 5.5 5.25c0 1.516-.701 2.5-1.328 3.259-.095.115-.184.22-.268.319-.207.245-.383.453-.541.681-.208.3-.33.565-.37.847a.751.751 0 0 1-1.485-.212c.084-.593.337-1.078.621-1.489.203-.292.45-.584.673-.848.075-.088.147-.173.213-.253.561-.679.985-1.32.985-2.304 0-2.06-1.637-3.75-4-3.75ZM5.75 12h4.5a.75.75 0 0 1 0 1.5h-4.5a.75.75 0 0 1 0-1.5ZM6 15.25a.75.75 0 0 1 .75-.75h2.5a.75.75 0 0 1 0 1.5h-2.5a.75.75 0 0 1-.75-.75Z\"></path></svg>Tip</p><p dir=\"auto\"><strong>Legacy Support</strong>: The engine gracefully falls back to parse old <code>#code=...</code> URLs, ensuring backward compatibility with any links generated prior to the v2.0 settings update.</p>\n</div>\n<hr>\n<div class=\"markdown-heading\" dir=\"auto\"><h2 class=\"heading-element\" dir=\"auto\">🛠️ Architecture Workflow</h2><a id=\"user-content-️-architecture-workflow\" class=\"anchor\" aria-label=\"Permalink: 🛠️ Architecture Workflow\" href=\"#️-architecture-workflow\"><svg data-component=\"Octicon\" class=\"octicon octicon-link\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" version=\"1.1\" width=\"16\" height=\"16\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><path d=\"m7.775 3.275 1.25-1.25a3.5 3.5 0 1 1 4.95 4.95l-2.5 2.5a3.5 3.5 0 0 1-4.95 0 .751.751 0 0 1 .018-1.042.751.751 0 0 1 1.042-.018 1.998 1.998 0 0 0 2.83 0l2.5-2.5a2.002 2.002 0 0 0-2.83-2.83l-1.25 1.25a.751.751 0 0 1-1.042-.018.751.751 0 0 1-.018-1.042Zm-4.69 9.64a1.998 1.998 0 0 0 2.83 0l1.25-1.25a.751.751 0 0 1 1.042.018.751.751 0 0 1 .018 1.042l-1.25 1.25a3.5 3.5 0 1 1-4.95-4.95l2.5-2.5a3.5 3.5 0 0 1 4.95 0 .751.751 0 0 1-.018 1.042.751.751 0 0 1-1.042.018 1.998 1.998 0 0 0-2.83 0l-2.5 2.5a1.998 1.998 0 0 0 0 2.83Z\"></path></svg></a></div>\n<section class=\"js-render-needs-enrichment render-needs-enrichment position-relative\" data-identity=\"b250b4cc-ccb2-49ab-9d7c-54f6c55bc30d\" data-host=\"https://viewscreen.githubusercontent.com\" data-src=\"https://viewscreen.githubusercontent.com/markdown/mermaid?docs_host=https%3A%2F%2Fdocs.github.com\" data-type=\"mermaid\" aria-label=\"mermaid rendered output container\">\n  <div class=\"js-render-enrichment-target\" data-json=\"{&quot;data&quot;:&quot;graph TD\\n    A[Monaco Editor] --&amp;gt;|Raw String| B(Parser Engine)\\n    B --&amp;gt;|Extracts| C[Tables Data]\\n    B --&amp;gt;|Extracts| D[Relationships]\\n    \\n    C --&amp;gt; E{Dagre Layout Engine}\\n    D --&amp;gt; E\\n    \\n    F[Zustand Store] --&amp;gt;|Settings: Gaps &amp;amp; Fonts| E\\n    \\n    E --&amp;gt;|Calculates X/Y &amp;amp; Bounds| G((React Virtual DOM))\\n    G --&amp;gt; H[Interactive Canvas UI]\\n    G --&amp;gt; I[Static SVG / PNG Export Engine]\\n&qu